cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI

The paper discusses the use of citation-based indicators in research evaluation, which is a common topic in several sub-categories of computer science. However, the focus on correlations between citation counts and quality scores suggests a stronger connection to sub-categories such as cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The simulations used in the study also involve mixing different disciplines, which could relate to sub-categories such as cs.CY (Computational Biology) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
